  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Management and Operation of Humanitarian Hubs in North-East Nigeria.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 2016, IOM has established humanitarian hubs in eight locations across Borno State, including Maiduguri, Gwoza, Bama, Ngala, Dikwa, Monguno, Banki, and Damasak. These hubs play a critical enabling role in the provision of life-saving humanitarian assistance by improving access to the 7.1 million people in need of assistance in north-east Nigeria. However, the cost-recovery mechanism to help sustain the humanitarian hubs does not raise sufficient funds to cover the costs. Through this project, IOM will ensure the continued operation and maintenance of MOSS/MORSS-compliant humanitarian hubs in deep-field locations with improved services to support humanitarian access to crisis-affected populations.</narrative>
  </description>
